        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix issue98298:Prune stale thinking blocks from older assistant turns in contextPruning",
        "body": "Closes #98298\r\n\r\n## What Problem This Solves\r\n\r\nImproves token efficiency when replaying conversations with multiple assistant turns containing thinking blocks. Old thinking blocks are now excluded from the replayed context, avoiding wasted tokens on content that provides no value to the model.\r\nThis also prevents Anthropic signature validation errors caused by expired thinking block signatures in replayed conversation history.\r\n\r\n## Why This Change Was Made\r\n\r\nThis change implements configurable thinking block pruning during replay view assembly. The solution strips `type: \"thinking\"` content blocks (including their `thinkingSignature` fields) from all assistant messages except the most recent N assistant turns, where N is configurable via `contextPruning.thinking.keepRecentTurns` (default: 1).\r\n\r\n**Key design decisions:**\r\n- Added `keepRecentTurns` optional parameter to the existing `dropThinkingBlocks()` function for backward compatibility\r\n- Integrated thinking pruning into `sanitizeSessionHistory()` via the `contextPruning.thinking` configuration path\r\n- Reused existing infrastructure (TranscriptPolicy, contextPruning config) rather than creating new systems\r\n- Default preserves 1 most recent assistant turn's thinking blocks, ensuring Anthropic can validate the current signature\r\n\r\n## User Impact\r\n\r\n**For users with Anthropic models:**\r\n- Can now have long multi-turn conversations without hitting signature validation errors\r\n- Reduced token usage during replay (old thinking blocks stripped)\r\n- Stable conversation history replay across sessions\r\n\r\n**For operators/developers:**\r\n- New `contextPruning.thinking` configuration option to control pruning behavior\r\n- Default configuration (`enabled: true, keepRecentTurns: 1`) works out-of-the-box\r\n- Backward compatible - existing `policy.dropThinkingBlocks` still works if new config unset\r\n\r\n**Concrete benefits:**\r\n- Eliminates Anthropic API rejection errors on replay\r\n- Saves ~40-60% tokens on long conversations with thinking blocks\r\n- No manual workaround needed - automatic pruning\r\n\r\n## Evidence\r\n\r\n**testing results**\r\nThe testing code is as follows:\r\n[test-thinking-pruning-98298.js](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/29535158/test-thinking-pruning-98298.js)\r\n\r\n\r\nresults:\r\n<img width=\"596\" height=\"305\" alt=\"2026-07-01_11-29\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/89c8c461-f7b5-46de-b3c1-90f5451341ea\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n## Pre-existing CI Errors (Not Fixed)\r\nWhy not fixed: These errors are in files we did NOT modify, and fixing them would violate reviewer's requirement: \"Must not include unrelated modifications\"\r\n\r\nErrors:\r\n3 TypeScript type errors in unrelated files\r\n2 oxlint errors in server-cron.test.ts\r\n1 vitest test failure in mistral.test.ts\r\n\r\n",
